orted the control and persecution of individual homoerotic behaviour in France and Quebec, this book makes the case that when it came to managing sexuality, the law helped construct the crime.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGay peoplexLegal status, laws, etc.zFrancexHistory. 0aGay peoplexLegal status, laws, etc.zQuébec (Province)xHistory. 0aGaysxLegal status, laws, etcxHistoryxFrancexFrancexQuébec. 0aGaysxLegal status, laws, etcxHistoryxQuébec (Province). 0aGaysxLegal status, laws, etczFrancexHistory. 0aGaysxLegal status, laws, etczQuébec (Province)xHistory. 0aHomosexualityxSocial aspectsxHistoryxFrance. 0aHomosexualityxSocial aspectsxHistoryxQuébec (Province). 0aHomosexualityxSocial aspectszFrancexHistory. 0aHomosexualityxSocial aspectszQuébec (Province)xHistory. 0aHomosexualityxSocial aspectszQuébec (Province)xHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh1 aAdam, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoth, Käthe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077481722640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774817226423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774817226/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV